        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 5:46PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles southeast of Pine Valley, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pine Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
